{"parse":{"title":"Christopher Green (art historian)","pageid":55735132,"revid":827555252,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Christopher Kenneth Green</b>, <a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_British_Academy\" title=\"Fellow of the British Academy\">FBA</a> (born 1943) is a British <a href=\"/wiki/History_of_art\" title=\"History of art\">art historian</a>, who was Professor of the History of Art at the <a href=\"/wiki/Courtauld_Institute_of_Art\" title=\"Courtauld Institute of Art\">Courtauld Institute of Art</a> between 1991 and 2008.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Early_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Early life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Career\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Career</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Honours\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Honours</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Personal_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Personal life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life\">Early life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Christopher_Green_(art_historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Early life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Christopher Kenneth Green was born in 1943,<sup id=\"cite_ref-WhWaWh_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WhWaWh-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> the second son of Frederic Ray Hilton Green, a civil servant with the <a href=\"/wiki/Colonial_Office\" title=\"Colonial Office\">Colonial Office</a> who served as Inspector of Mines in <a href=\"/wiki/Kenya\" title=\"Kenya\">Kenya</a> and later lived at <a href=\"/wiki/Epsom_Downs\" title=\"Epsom Downs\">Epsom Downs</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Surrey\" title=\"Surrey\">Surrey</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-bp_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bp-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Green was educated at <a href=\"/wiki/Christ%27s_College,_Cambridge\" title=\"Christ&#39;s College, Cambridge\">Christ's College, Cambridge</a>, graduating in 1966 with a <a href=\"/wiki/Bachelor_of_Arts\" title=\"Bachelor of Arts\">Bachelor of Arts</a> (BA) degree; he then completed a <a href=\"/wiki/Master_of_Arts\" title=\"Master of Arts\">Master of Arts</a> (MA) degree at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_London\" title=\"University of London\">University of London</a>;<sup id=\"cite_ref-WhWaWh_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WhWaWh-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> in 1973, he was awarded a <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Philosophy\" title=\"Doctor of Philosophy\">Doctor of Philosophy</a> (PhD) degree by the <a href=\"/wiki/Courtauld_Institute_of_Art\" title=\"Courtauld Institute of Art\">Courtauld Institute of Art</a>, University of London, for his thesis \"<a href=\"/wiki/Fernand_L%C3%A9ger\" title=\"Fernand L\u00e9ger\">Fernand L\u00e9ger</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/Paris\" title=\"Paris\">Parisian</a> <i><a href=\"/wiki/Avant-garde\" title=\"Avant-garde\">avant-garde</a></i>, 1909\u20131921\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> supervised by the artist and writer <a href=\"/wiki/John_Golding_(artist_and_writer)\" title=\"John Golding (artist and writer)\">John Golding</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Golding_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Golding-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Career\">Career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Christopher_Green_(art_historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Green's first curatorial work was with Golding for the <a href=\"/wiki/Tate\" title=\"Tate\">Tate</a> exhibition <i>L\u00e9ger and Purist Paris</i> in 1970.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Golding_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Golding-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> He remained at the Courtauld as a lecturer after completing his PhD and was later appointed a <a href=\"/wiki/Reader_(academic_rank)\" title=\"Reader (academic rank)\">reader</a> there. In 1991, the Institute appointed him Professor of the History of Art,<sup id=\"cite_ref-britac_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-britac-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> a post he held until his retirement in 2008. For the 1997\u20138 academic year, he was a <a href=\"/wiki/Leverhulme_Trust\" title=\"Leverhulme Trust\">Leverhulme</a> Research Fellow, and between 2001 and 2010, he was Trustee of <a href=\"/wiki/National_Museums_Liverpool\" title=\"National Museums Liverpool\">National Museums Liverpool</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WhWaWh_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WhWaWh-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Green curated the <a href=\"/wiki/Juan_Gris\" title=\"Juan Gris\">Juan Gris</a> exhibition at the <a href=\"/wiki/Whitechapel_Gallery\" title=\"Whitechapel Gallery\">Whitechapel Gallery</a> in 1992, the <a href=\"/wiki/Roger_Fry\" title=\"Roger Fry\">Roger Fry</a> exhibition at the Courtauld Institute in 1999, the <a href=\"/wiki/Henri_Rousseau\" title=\"Henri Rousseau\">Henri Rousseau</a> exhibition at the <a href=\"/wiki/Tate_Modern\" title=\"Tate Modern\">Tate Modern</a> in Paris and Washington in 2005, the <a href=\"/wiki/Pablo_Picasso\" title=\"Pablo Picasso\">Picasso</a> exhibition in Barcelona in 2008, the Modern Antiquity exhibition at the <a href=\"/wiki/J._Paul_Getty_Museum\" title=\"J. Paul Getty Museum\">J. Paul Getty Museum</a> in 2011 and, most recently, the <a href=\"/wiki/Piet_Mondrian\" title=\"Piet Mondrian\">Mondrian</a>\u2013<a href=\"/wiki/Ben_Nicholson\" title=\"Ben Nicholson\">Nicholson</a> exhibition at the Courtauld in 2012.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WhWaWh_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WhWaWh-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Christopher_Green_(art_historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Green's major works include:<sup id=\"cite_ref-britac_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-britac-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Golding_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Golding-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li><i>L\u00e9ger and the Avant-Garde</i> (Yale University Press, 1976).</li>\n<li><i>Cubism and its Enemies: Modern Movements and Reaction in French Art 1916\u201328</i> (Yale University Press, 1987).</li>\n<li><i>Art in France 1900\u20131940</i> (Yale University Press, 2000).</li>\n<li><i>Picasso: Architecture and Vertigo</i> (Yale University Press, 2005).</li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Honours\">Honours</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Christopher_Green_(art_historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Honours\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In 1999, Green was elected a <a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_British_Academy\" title=\"Fellow of the British Academy\">Fellow of the British Academy</a>, the United Kingdom's national academy for the humanities and social sciences.<sup id=\"cite_ref-britac_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-britac-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Personal_life\">Personal life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Christopher_Green_(art_historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Personal life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 1968, Green married Charlotte Hannah (born 1944), younger daughter of Lt-Col. <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Oliver_Robert_Marne_Sebag-Montefiore&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Oliver Robert Marne Sebag-Montefiore (page does not exist)\">Oliver Robert Marne Sebag-Montefiore</a> (1915\u20131993), <a href=\"/wiki/Order_of_the_British_Empire\" title=\"Order of the British Empire\">OBE</a>, who was President of the <a href=\"/wiki/Jewish_Care\" title=\"Jewish Care\">Jewish Welfare Board</a>. They have two children: one son and one daughter.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WhWaWh_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WhWaWh-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-bp_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bp-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Christopher_Green_(art_historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-WhWaWh-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-WhWaWh_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-WhWaWh_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-WhWaWh_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-WhWaWh_1-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-WhWaWh_1-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ukwhoswho.com/view/article/oupww/whoswho/U41547\">\"Green, Prof. Christopher Kenneth\"</a>, <i>Who's Who 2017</i>, A &amp; C Black (online edn, Oxford University Press, November 2016). Retrieved 7 November 2017.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-bp-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-bp_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-bp_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Burke's Peerage</i> (2003), vol. 3, p. 4038.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>The Colonial Office List</i> (London: HMSO, 1948), p. 451.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Marriages\", <i>Times</i> (London), 31 July 1967, p. 8.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"e